customers.about:
Established more than a century ago, the Scheller College of Business has a distinguished history as part of a world-renowned technical research university.

The College is internationally recognized as a leader in business education that’s grounded in a deep understanding of how advances in technology affect the way business is conducted. We provide undergraduate, graduate, doctoral, professional, and corporate education for some of the future’s brightest business leaders, equipping them with the analytical skills to assess opportunities and apply appropriate technologies for a competitive advantage.

people.about: I have been working in the field for over five years. With an undergraduate degree from the University in 2005, and over ten years' experience in the field I love crafting beautiful, unique products for the University's teams.
AFM & Spectroscopy Support; AFM, XPS, Raman
Facility Manager II – Pettit Microelectronics & Marcus Nanotechnology Building

roles.about: Undergraduate Students are the heart and soul of our institution, numbering at around 12,000.
Masters Students pursue advanced degrees in our University's many programs, totalling at around 4,000.
RA's are responsible for managing the daily affairs of campus life in our dormatories.
Our designers articulate the University's Brand Identity across print and digital media.
